SQL Learning Roadmap (Beginner to Master) – MySQL

LEVEL 1: SQL BASICS – FOUNDATION
1. What is SQL? What is MySQL?
2. SQL data types (INT, VARCHAR, DATE, etc.)
3. Creating a database and selecting it (CREATE DATABASE, USE)
4. Creating a table (CREATE TABLE)
5. Inserting data (INSERT INTO)
6. Viewing data (SELECT *, SELECT column)
7. Filtering data (WHERE)
8. Sorting results (ORDER BY)
9. Limiting results (LIMIT)
10. Using DISTINCT to remove duplicates

LEVEL 2: SQL LOGIC & CONDITIONS
11. Comparison operators (=, <, >, <=, <>)
12. Logical operators (AND, OR, NOT)
13. Wildcards with LIKE (% and _)
14. IN and NOT IN
15. BETWEEN and NOT BETWEEN
16. IS NULL and IS NOT NULL

LEVEL 3: MODIFYING DATA
17. Updating records (UPDATE ... SET ... WHERE)
18. Deleting records (DELETE FROM ... WHERE)
19. Truncating vs Deleting (TRUNCATE TABLE)
20. Dropping a table or database (DROP TABLE, DROP DATABASE)

LEVEL 4: ADVANCED SELECT QUERIES
21. Aggregate functions (COUNT, SUM, AVG, MIN, MAX)
22. Grouping data (GROUP BY)
23. Filtering groups (HAVING)
24. Aliases with AS for columns and tables
25. Nested queries / subqueries (in SELECT, WHERE, FROM)
26. Case statements (CASE WHEN THEN ELSE END)

LEVEL 5: MULTIPLE TABLES & JOINS
27. Primary keys and foreign keys
28. Table relationships (1:1, 1:N, N:N)
29. Inner Join (INNER JOIN)
30. Left Join (LEFT JOIN)
31. Right Join (RIGHT JOIN)
32. Full Join (simulate with UNION in MySQL)
33. Cross Join
34. Self Join

LEVEL 6: DATABASE DESIGN & TABLE STRUCTURE
35. Database normalization (1NF, 2NF, 3NF – simplified)
36. Creating relationships with FOREIGN KEY
37. Default values and constraints (NOT NULL, DEFAULT, UNIQUE)
38. Auto increment (AUTO_INCREMENT)
39. Data integrity and constraint errors
40. Using SHOW TABLES, DESCRIBE, INFORMATION_SCHEMA

LEVEL 7: INDEXES, PERFORMANCE, SECURITY
41. What is an index? Creating an index (CREATE INDEX)
42. Checking slow queries and optimizing them
43. User management: creating users, assigning permissions
44. Backups and exporting data (mysqldump, EXPORT)
45. Importing data (LOAD DATA INFILE, IMPORT)
46. SQL injection awareness (basic security concept)

LEVEL 8: REAL-WORLD SQL PRACTICE
47. Build a small user database (users, orders, products)
48. Write queries like: “top 5 customers this month”
49. Clean dirty data (replace empty, fix typos)
50. Create summary reports (total sales, average price, etc.)

BONUS (Optional Advanced)
- Stored procedures and functions
- Triggers
- Views
- Transactions and rollback
- Common Table Expressions (CTEs)
- Window functions (ROW_NUMBER(), RANK(), etc.)